The paper deals with adversarial representation learning, which is a popular topic in machine learning and computer vision. The use of kernel methods and spectral learning suggests a focus on optimization and theoretical analysis, which are common themes in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The experiments on UCI, Extended Yale B, and CIFAR-100 datasets indicate a focus on computer vision, which suggests the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of deep neural networks and iterative minimax optimization suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, which suggests the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the study of invariance and bias suggests a focus on security and privacy, which suggests the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
